<br>
1. To get decent mana/dmg efficientcy you would need to pull 5 mobs. This is a problem because BoF only hits 4 at a time. That means a minimun of 2 BoF casts.<br>
<br>
2. At lvl 49 with pretty nice +mana equipment and 200int you might have about 2500 mana (this is about 350 +mana, a lot for lvl 49) here is your best case scenario with 5 mobs.<br>
<br>
Total mana  2500<br>
2 BoF -150 mana<br>
4 Wrath -2000 mana<br>
<br>
That leaves you with about 350 mana left for clean up on up to 5 mobs that you have done 1952 damage to. If even 2 mobs survive, the highest nuke you could use for 2 mobs would be lvl 39 Lightning shock. Granted, you would still have harvest, but at this point you are shooting another 75 mana to BoF again as you will be pushing you luck with snare breaking at this point. So you will be left with just enough mana to cast 1 more Al'crapwhores and pray you kill of the bunch. Multiple mob surviving at this point would probably mean dead. <br>
<br>
IMHO unless you can find some VERY low blues with HP in the 1600-1800 range it would be suicide to try using Al'crapwhores to kite. <p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Wandor Kilbringer<br>Channeler of the 54th Conclave<br>Vini, Vidi, Nuki</b></span><br>
